                        <collation>
                           <p>
                           35 quires: i10 (folios 1-10), ii10 (folios 11-20), iii12 (folios
                              21-32), iv-xvii10 (folios 33-172), xviii8 (folios 173-180), xix8-1
                              (folios 181-187), xx-xxxiv10 (folios 188-337), xxxv8 (folios 338-343),
                              after folio 342 - 2 unfoliated leaves.
                        </p>
                        </collation>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout>
                           <p>Columns: 1;
                                                  ruled lines: 19;
                                                  written lines: 19; Uniform layout.Initial words written in larger characters.Catchwords (decorated) at the end of the quires.Hair side and flesh side are distinguishable. The manuscript is imperfect at the beginning, and there is a gap after
                              folio 152. Erased text (folio 26v). Ruling by hard point (bifolium by bifolium) and pricking (in outer
                              margins only) are visible.</p>
                        </layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <scriptDesc>
